In my use case we wanted to disable all reverts on a specific model, so i implemented this class that extends the VersionAdmin:
```

from reversion.admin import VersionAdmin

class RevertNotSupportedValidationException(Exception):
    pass


class ReadonlyReversionAdmin(VersionAdmin):
    def _reversion_revisionform_view(self, request, *args, **kwargs):
        if request.method == "POST":
            raise RevertNotSupportedValidationException("Revert is not supported for this model")
        return super()._reversion_revisionform_view(request, *args, **kwargs)

```

Using it instead of the VersionAdmin will disable the revert on the model.

